{
  "texts": [
    "The F-score is a harmonic mean of precision (the percentage of texts the model identified as belonging to a category that actually belong to it as per the gold standard) and recall (the percentage of texts belonging to the category as per the gold standard that the model identified as such) (Aggarwal, 2018).",
    "A higher F-score indicates better predictions, with 1 indicating a perfect match to human coding.",
    "To evaluate the performance across multiple categories in our coding schemes, we report micro-averaged F-scores. foot_10",
    "We use four datasets and coding schemes as case studies for our method comparison.",
    "These include a dataset of 2,000 texts from an online marketplace coded for seven motives of their authors, two Twitter datasets containing 3,832 and 24,783 texts and coded for moral norm expression and the presence of hate speech, respectively, and a dataset of 10,000 Reddit posts coded for the expression of six different emotions."
  ]
}